0036|- [HelpText]
0037|*As an extension of editorial computing, various numerical conversions
0038|*may be performed by activating expressions like
0039|*        <number_or_word>(<unit1>:<unit2>)=_
S   |         <              > <     > <     >
0041|*For example, 440(yard:meter)=402.336 gives 440 yards as 402.336 meters.
0043|*In place of <number_or_word>, no composite expressions are accepted.
S   |             <              >
0044|*If <number_or_word> is missing, '1' is used as default.
S   |    <              >
0045|*For example, 1(yard:meter)=0.9144  (yard:meter)=0.9144
0047|*Multiple activations occur along the rules of editorial computing
0048|*by using '.=' instead of '='. For example,
0049|*   (ton:kg).=_     (pound:kg).=                  (pound:ounce).=
0050|*gives
0051|*   (ton:kg).=1000  (pound:kg).=0.45358541666624  (pound:ounce).=16
0053|*If a conversion between unsuitable units like (kg:m)=  is attempted,
0054|*an error message 'Conversion from kg to m is impossible!' is displayed.
0056|*When appropriate, the prefixes of the International System like
0057|*'mega' and 'micro' are recognized. Examples: (megaton:ton)=1000000
0058|*(nanometer:ngstr”m)=1 (femtosecond:sec)=1e-015
0060|*The data base for units of measurement is the edit field MEASURES.EDT
0061|*in the \SYS subdirectory of Survo. This field lists the possible units
0062|*with pertinent information in alphabetic order. The user can edit this
0063|*field by following instructions given in the same edit field.
