0080|- [HelpText]
0081|*Converting integers from a base to another:
0082|*Examples:
0083|*   1988(10:2)=11111000100    1988 from base 10 to base 2
0084|*   11111000100(2:10)=1988    11111000100 from base 2 to base 10
0085|*   254(10:8)=376             254 is 376 as an octal (base 8) number
0086|*   254(10:16)=FE             254 is FE as a hexadecimal number
0087|*   7C4(16:10)=1988
0088|*   FFFF(hex:dec)=65535       hex and dec are allowed instead of 16 and 10
0089|*   777(oct:bin)=111111111    oct and bin are allowed instead of 8 and 2
0091|*Max. base is 36. In bases >10, digits are
S   |                           >
0092|*  0,1,2,3,4,5,6,8,9,A,B,C,D,...,Z .
